Theorem~\ref{thm_Kpq-} shows that for $2 \leq p \leq q$ the graph $K_{p,q}^-$ is DS and its proof seems useful for the study on the graph $K_{p,q}^+.$ However, Remark~\ref{rem_Kpq-} immediately gives a family of $K_{p,q}^+$'s which are not DS. In this section we present a sufficient and necessary condition to determine whether $K_{p,q}^+$ is DS or not for each pair $(p,q).$ Furthermore, we also find the all non-isomorphic cospectral graphs of every $K_{p,q}^+$ which is not DS.



