The following lemma helps us to exhaustedly enumerate $K_{p, q}^+$ which has a non-isomorphic cospectral graph by using Theorem~\ref{thm_Kpq+}.
\begin{lem}\label{lem_abb't}
Let $3 \leq p \leq q$  be integers. Then the quadratic polynomial in \eqref{quadratic_polynomial}
has two integral roots $p'', q''\in [2, \infty)$ if and only if
there exist nonnegative integers $a,b,b',t$ with $1 \leq b,b' < a,$ $\text{gcd}(a,b)=1,$ $bb' \equiv 1~(\text{mod}~a),$ and $bb'+t \geq 2$ such that $p,q,p'',q''$ can be written as
\begin{eqnarray}
p&=&b(a-b)t+bb'+\frac{b(1-bb')}{a}+1,
\label{eq_abb't_p} \\
q&=&a^2t+ab',
\label{eq_abb't_q} \\
p''&=&bq/a+1,~~~\text{and}~~~q''=q+2-bq/a.
\label{eq_abb't_p''q''}
\end{eqnarray}
\end{lem}
